next

1.3.0
  xcreature:
    Added: online_iter() - safe game_objects_iter with db.storage fallback for vanilla/AOEngine
  Compatibility:
    Removed: modded exes requirement. Works with vanilla Anomaly 1.5.3, Demonized, Demonized MT, AOEngine. Tested with GAMMA, EFP, Zona.

1.2.7
  Summary: Species identification, squad control hardening, bounded cache
  xsquad:
    Added: reassert_target(squad, target) restores scripted_target if another mod overwrote it between scans.
    Changed: control_squad, target_actor, release_squad, reassert_target clear __lock (AP does not use it; scripted_target alone routes to specific_update).
    Fixed: fatal crash in _resolve_commander when non-squad server object arrives via squad_on_update callback (clsid guard in _check_permanent, field guard in _resolve_commander)
  xcreature:
    Added: get_mutant_species(input) returns the base species string for any entity. Accepts squads, server objects, game objects, or IDs. Handles modded exe clsid ambiguity via section prefix fallback. Stalker squads rejected at zero cost via player_id check.
    Added: get_mutant_variant(input) returns the full NPC variant section (e.g. "bloodsucker_red_strong").
  xttltable:
    Added: clock injection (opts.clock) for ttl_table, ttl_counter, token_bucket. Callers can pass game-time or custom clock functions. Default remains os.clock (zero luabind).
    Added: create_fifo_cache(opts) creates a bounded cache with ring buffer eviction. Oldest entry evicted when capacity is reached.

1.2.6
  Summary: Set operations
  xtable:
    Added: merge(...) - set union of hash tables. Variadic, nil-safe, returns new table.
    Added: subtract(base, ...) - set difference. Returns base keys minus all keys in remaining args.

1.2.5
  xlevel:
    Added: vertex-to-level cache in get_level_id (gvid -> level_id, immutable, populated on first lookup)
  xsquad:
    Added: is_protected(squad, opts) - public composite guard with shared commander context, returns (bool, reason, detail, name)
    Added: exclude_filter_reason opt for custom filter label in is_protected
    Added: story_id squads cache section_name in _static_cache (eliminates repeated string alloc)
    Changed: _check_protected removed, _squad_base_valid delegates to is_protected
    Changed: is_externally_scripted renamed to is_scripted, checks engine/vanilla fields only
    Added: exclude_filter option in is_protected (generic function filter, runs first)
    Changed: exclude_externally_scripted renamed to exclude_scripted in find_squad/find_squads
    Removed: find_online_squads (dead code, zero callers)

1.2.4
  X-Ray:
    Added: timed event scheduling works correctly with major modpacks (globals resolve at call time for demonized_time_events compatibility)
  xmath:
    Added: prd_chance pseudo-random distribution (Dota 2 PRD algorithm, reduces streak variance)
    Added: chance() no longer writes diagnostic output to console
  xsquad:
    Added: is_task_target, O(1) task squad check with bounty/hostage member fallback
    Added: is_permanent_squad, static identity guard (story, trader, named_npc, empty, cached)
    Added: has_active_role, dynamic role guard (task_giver, companion)
    Changed: find_squad/find_squads/find_online_squads use 4 granular guard flags
    Changed: distance bounds use inclusive upper (Demonized pattern)
    Removed: is_unscriptable_squad (replaced by is_permanent_squad + has_active_role)
    Removed: exclude_unscriptable opt (replaced by granular flags)
    Fixed: find_online_squads re-evaluating rejected squads on every member NPC
    Fixed: release_squads crash on stale SIMBOARD IDs after delete_all + repopulate
    Fixed: release_squads deleting task target squads (assault, bounty, delivery)
  xlog:
    Added: deadbanding, identical consecutive log lines collapsed to "ROW(N times)"
  xtable:
    Added: check_lock, peek lock availability without acquiring
  xslice:
    Added: xslice, time-sliced array iteration across frames (deferred drain, AddUniqueCall scheduling, 3-return protocol)
  MCM:
    Changed: MCM visual refresh
    Fixed: Russian MCM encoding restored (windows-1251)
    Changed: xlibs.version() renamed to xlibs.get_version()

1.2.3
  Fixed: xsmart.get_proximity unguarded game_graph() NULL singleton during transitions
  Fixed: xobject.go missing level.present() guard for level.object_by_id
  Fixed: xsmart.dump_smarts 3-level nesting violation (guard clause flatten)
  Fixed: xcreature.is_npc orphan docblock removed
  Fixed: xpda dead not-level guards removed (5 instances)
  Changed: xstash.loot_stash_to_npc renamed to xstash.loot_stash (removed unused npc_id parameter)

1.2.2
  Added: xtime.game_sec game-seconds since epoch (cached start_time, 2 luabind)
  Added: xlibs.is_compatible semver compatibility check (same major, actual >= required)
  Changed: xsmart.has_capacity accepts incoming parameter for in-transit squad counting
  Changed: depgate pattern from == exact match to is_compatible (patch bumps no longer cascade)

1.2.1
  Added: xstash.get_stash_items read-only stash contents getter (non-destructive parse)
  Added: xsquad.is_externally_scripted (checks scripted_target, __lock, registered_with_warfare, action_condlist, random_targets)
  Fixed: xdata.unscriptable_npcs typo for Dead City barman (Aslan) preventing unscriptable guard

1.2.0
  Added: xconst - centralized X-Ray engine sentinel constants (INVALID_ENTITY_ID, INVALID_LEVEL_VERTEX_ID)
  Added: xttltable.create_token_bucket - per-key O(1) rate limiter with fractional accumulation
  Added: xttltable token bucket peek() - O(1) availability check without consuming a token
  Added: xsmart.get_smart_squads - returns raw SIMBOARD squads table for a smart terrain
  Changed: xlevel, xsquad, xinspect use xconst instead of file-local magic numbers
  Changed: xsmart.get_smart_squads accepts smart_id (number) instead of entity (saves 1 luabind)
  Fixed: xobject.get_box_size crash when ammo section doesn't exist in system_ini

1.0.5
  xlevel pcall removal, nil guard improvements.
  Fixed: get_game_hours unnecessary pcall, replaced with level.present() guard
  Fixed: get_current_level_name missing level.present() guard

1.0.4
  Renamed: is_protected -> is_unscriptable (xcreature), is_protected_squad -> is_unscriptable_squad (xsquad)
  Renamed: xdata.protected_npcs -> xdata.unscriptable_npcs
  Renamed: exclude_protected -> exclude_unscriptable in find_squad/find_squads/find_online_squads opts
  Added: xcreature.is_task_giver(obj) - checks NPC ID and squad ID against active tasks
  Fixed: xsquad task giver check now covers dialog tasks (commander_id)

1.0.3
  Added: xlibs.version() API for dependency checking
  Added: MCM info page showing version and description

1.0.2
  Fixed: xstash.find_stashes excludes player-created stashes (inv_backpack)

1.0.1
  Fixed: xsquad.is_protected_squad excludes companion squads

1.0.0
  First release. 19 utility modules for Anomaly Lua modding.
  Added: xcreature - entity identification and fluent query iterator
  Added: xsquad - squad search, scripted control, release, iteration
  Added: xsmart - smart terrain queries, faction, capacity, arrival, conquest
  Added: xlevel - level/map, game time, location names
  Added: xobject - server object resolution, offline item creation
  Added: xstash - stash discovery, looting, filling
  Added: xdata - protected NPC/squad lookup tables
  Added: xtable - table utilities, locks, memoize
  Added: xttltable - TTL tables and sliding window counters
  Added: xmath - probability, sampling, weighted choice
  Added: xstring - string interpolation
  Added: xlog - buffered file logging
  Added: xprofiler - microsecond code profiling
  Added: xtrace - trace ID generation
  Added: xinspect - deep inspection
  Added: xbus - pub/sub event bus
  Added: xevent - runtime function hooking
  Added: xpda - PDA messages and map markers
  Added: xmcm - MCM config getters and loaders
